  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT349-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">parattaimāṭṭup pirintu vanta talaimakaṉ kēṭkum aṇmaiyaṉākat tōḻikkuk
          kiḻatti kūṟiyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER to the confidante, while HE was close
          [enough] to hear, since he came after having separated on account of another woman. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT349">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> aṭumpavi ḻaṇimalar citaiya mīṉaruntun</l>
          <l> taṭantā ṇārai yirukku mekkart</l>
          <l> taṇṇan tuṟaivaṟ ṟoṭuttu nannalaṅ</l>
          <l> koḷvā meṉṟi tōḻi koḷvā</l>
          <l> miṭukka ṇañci yirantōr vēṇṭiya</l>
          <l> koṭuttavai tāveṉac colliṉu</l>
          <l> miṉṉā tōnam miṉṉuyi riḻappē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>After having linked [it] to the man from the cool ghat</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with dunes, where broad-footed herons are perched,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">that eat fish [and] spoil the opening adorning blossoms</l>
          <l rend="indent9">of the Aṭumpu,</l>
          <l>“we'll take our innocence”, you may say, friend, “we'll take [it back]”.</l>
          <l rend="indent">Even if [we] said “give those things [back]”, having offered</l>
          <l rend="indent2">them as they were needed by one who begged,</l>
          <l rend="indent7">for fear of [his] distress,</l>
          <l>[is that] less undear than the loss of our dear life?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
